title: Called Doug Storey, we found a roughing pump had tripped off. Beamline pumping down.
text: There are two sets of Turbo/roughing pumps in this area. I had found one turbo turned off, and turned it on, but it turns out that one had already been off. Doug pulled a valve between the second turbo that I had turned on and a roughing pump, and the area began to pump down again. We've been gradually raising the photon energy for TMO - instructions inside
text: The script shifts the relevant girders in order to change the photon energy by a user-requested amount. We could do this via the taper GUI of course, but the script is quite convenient. To use the script, open a Matlab terminal and cd to /home/physics/dcesar/taper_tools. From this directory you can run the script with the following command: shift_k(15,[[26:34] [36:43]],'PSfiles',cellData) Here the first argument (15) is the number of electron volts by which you're changing the energy, the next few arguments tell the script which girders to move, and the final couple of arguments are opaque to me. You will need to initialize the cellData argument before running the script, which you can do by copying the following, pasting it into the Matlab terminal, and executing it: if ~exist('cellData') addpath ( genpath ( '/home/physics/nuhn/wrk/matlab' ), genpath ( '/home/physics/wolf/PhaseShifterManagerR2' ) ); addpath ( genpath ( '/home/physics/wolf/PhaseShifterManager' ) ); cellData={}; cellData.param=cell_data_param(); cellData.PSdata=sxr_ps_manage_init(cellData.param); %or hxr_ps_manage_init(); cellData.undulatorLine='SXR';%end init end
